  "texts": [
    "However, we screened nearly 3,000 articles in total and systematically analyzed 89 articles, providing a comprehensive overview of the current state of LLMs in patient care, even if some articles could have been missed.",
    "Third, the rapid development and advancement of LLMs make it difficult to keep this systematic review up to date.",
    "For example, Gemini 1.5 Pro was published in February 2024, and corresponding articles are not included in this review, which synthesized articles from 2022 to 2023.",
    "Continued updates will be essential to monitor emerging areas and limitations in this rapidly evolving field.",
    "In conclusion, this review provides a systematic overview of current LLM applications and limitations in patient care."
  ],
